  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The pronounced effect of goiter on the esophagus needs further exploration, as the mechanisms
      by which goiter leads to swallowing difficulties are unknown. By investigating esophageal
      motility using high resolution esophageal manometry before and after thyroidectomy we seek to
      examine the impact of the goiter mass on the esophagus and swallowing with six months
      follow-up.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
